Can I have your attention? Okay real quick let me give a back story to these photos @melodiesbyminda took of me! So she spent the entire day tagging along with me on a shoot I did and we got back to mine tired but still a little energized from the shoot. I showed her an inspo pic from Lori Harvey and told her I wanted to shoot something like that. As soon as I said that she had a plan and said okay we doing this tonight! Step by step we started putting the little look together from the hair to the jewelry to use and even lipstick. One little problem though? My little top was too small for my babies so we had to go on a hunt for boob tape at like 9pm 😂 from searching all around Walmart to going to shoppers. Anyways long story short, we got boob tape, lost it on our way back only to find that I had some of my own. At some point during the entire adventure I gave up on the whole idea but my girl said nope this MUST work and she made sure it did! 
I had the most fun and it reminded me so much of my beginning days, what it feels like to build an outfit or well a look from scratch and just shoot for the fun of it. So thank you @melodiesbyminda for these photos and talk it was her first time with a camera ever and she did a good job if I do say so myself 😍 check my stories for some other photos that didn’t make it to the gram. 

How did we do guys? And swipe for the inspo 😉

So I was hanging with my girl this past weekend and I showed her some of these pics.. she complemented me and asked how I make cheap clothes look so expensive. I told her and I’m gonna tell y’all now, style is style! It doesn’t matter what you’re wearing or how much it cost, if you own it and flaunt it and are confident enough you will make ANYTHING look expensive. Also just because something is cheap doesn’t mean it’s bad quality and vice versa for expensive clothes. What I look for when shopping for clothes is quality and how it’ll make me feel. 
Some of my nicest clothes are from brands with no names and I don’t give a hoot, I’ll still wear them and look cool Af. How you put outfits together matters, how you accessorize matters and most importantly, how you carry yourself in that outfit matters. That’s why I’ll always look expensive even if I’m wearing a $20 wig from Amazon or clothes from “fast fashion” brands. 
Thank you for coming to my TED talk ❤️ 
Bag, shoes, choker and bracelet are all from @hm innovation collection as well as past studio collections 
Sunglasses and outfit from @aliexpress (who gon check me) or if you got it like that you can get the same pants from @theattico 😉

Jacket in some of the pics is from @thenorthface and literally belongs to my photographer @woo_media (he gave me to wear because I was cold only to see that it went flawlessly with the outfit so we went with it lol) I love how spontaneous our shoots are. 

This is probably the longest caption I’ve ever had lol but I just felt like giving done backstory ☺️❤️ if you made it this far you’re a real one and have a lovely weekend!

I’m in a very weird space content wise, the joy/drive/passion I had for it years ago has been sliced in half and I don’t know why myself. Even these pics I almost didn’t shoot them and I had to psych myself up to get up and put my makeup on. This is why I have been very scarce on the TL lately. I get ideas sometimes and I just don’t even feel like executing them or I execute them and lose my memory card 😭 so back to not having anything to post. I don’t know if it’s burn out or just me moving to a post content creation phase in my life. I’ve seen it with some of my peers on here, posting less or just posting less on here… been battling this feeling for months and I hope it passes but if it doesn’t then so be it, on to the next passion or hobby that’ll light my heart on fire. I get dms of people checking in on me asking me if I’m okay and truth is that while sometimes I might not be, even the times when I am I just don’t want to post or have anything I feel is worth posting if you get what I mean. I know it’s been a while since I spilled my guts on here but I really didn’t have a caption so decided to be a little open. Anyways that aside, I have a trip soon that I’m excited for so hopefully you’ll see more of me depending on how things play out ☺️
